info.name: Spinal cord, medial motor cell column
info.description: The medial motor cell column of the spinal cord is part of the gray matter of the ventral or anterior horn of the spinal cord at all levels of the spinal cord.  It is located medially in the ventral horn and contains those lower motor neurons that innervate axial structures.
info.item: /Sections/Thin, Spinal Cord to Cerebrum/1 Sacral cord, middle
/Sections/Thin, Spinal Cord to Cerebrum/2 Lumbar cord, middle
